            <title>[HBASE-2683] Make it obvious in the documentation that ZooKeeper needs permanent storage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2683</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If our users let HBase manage ZK, they probably won&apos;t bother combing through hbase-default.xml to figure that they need to set hbase.zookeeper.property.dataDir to something else than /tmp. It probably happened to deinspanjer in prod today and that&apos;s a show stopper.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix would be, at least, to improve the Getting Started documentation to include that configuration in the &quot;Fully-Distributed Operation&quot; section.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
